INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (439051, 'I used to sing in church, too. Not like in the choir or anything, but for people around the church... on the church bus going home and Christmas plays.', 69359, 0), (439052, 'I love Halloween, trick or treating and decorating the house. And I love Thanksgiving, because of the football and the fall weather. And of course, I love Christmas - that''s my favorite of all!', 69761, 0), (439053, 'Everybody loves a good Christmas song if you do it right.', 69924, 0), (439054, 'Every Christmas Eve, the elves will come and give us a new pair of pajamas.', 69924, 0), (439055, 'The vocal arrangements are a big part of the formula for a Bad Religion song - layered harmonies and background vocals. So when I start to describe the elements of Bad Religion''s sound, it starts to sound like a Christmas choir.', 10504, 0), (439056, 'Like my dad, I have a Christmas party most years. I like to celebrate and see as many people as possible.', 2398, 0), (439057, 'It can''t be overstated how wonderful it is not to have to audition any more. Any actor will tell you, it''s like Christmas.', 70267, 0), (439058, 'I can''t tell you how scary it can be walking onto a movie and suddenly joining this family, it''s like going to somebody else''s Christmas dinner, everyone knows everyone, and you''re there and you''re not quite sure what you''re supposed to be doing.', 8174, 0), (439059, 'Faith is salted and peppered through everything at Christmas. And I love at least one night by the Christmas tree to sing and feel the quiet holiness of that time that''s set apart to celebrate love, friendship, and God''s gift of the Christ child.', 64661, 0), (439060, 'Come Christmas Eve, we usually go to my mom and dad''s. Everybody brings one gift and then we play that game when we all steal it from each other. Some are really cool, others are useful and some are a bit out there.', 64661, 0), (439061, 'Most of the soap operas always use the Christmas special to kill huge quantities of their characters. So they have trams coming off their rails, or cars slamming into each other or burning buildings. It''s a general clean-out.', 11190, 0), (439062, 'Black Friday is not another bad hair day in Wall Street. It''s the term used by American retailers to describe the day after the Thanksgiving Holiday, seen as the semi-official start of Christmas shopping season.', 69223, 0), (439063, 'I remember a great America where we made everything. There was a time when the only thing you got from Japan was a really bad cheap transistor radio that some aunt gave you for Christmas.', 863, 0), (439064, 'I had a great AP U.S. History teacher in Pittsburgh. We still exchange Christmas cards. She was the first teacher who said I was a good writer - and I''d never heard that before. And so I remember that, and I remember that level of loving the material and really loving writing about it.', 25063, 0), (439065, 'It was, you know, probably 80 degrees out in L.A., and my dad took me outside and there was snow. At the time, I thought, ''Every kid doesn''t have snow in their backyard on Christmas?''', 900, 0), (439066, 'Well, the album ''Intuition'' is out and just went platinum officially. So I think to have the music doing what it''s doing right now, man, it''s the ultimate. Nobody is really selling records out there but we are at a million records and we dropped it at Christmas, so we are just trying to get that thing to like two million, you know.', 68131, 0), (439067, 'I''m bad on Valentine''s Day, but even worse on Christmas. I go shopping at nine o''clock on December 24th every year. Nobody else is there. I''m in Toys''R''Us all by myself. I get there five minutes before closing.', 68131, 0), (439068, 'Christmas is the time when kids tell Santa what they want and adults pay for it. Deficits are when adults tell government what they want and their kids pay for it.', 50452, 0), (439069, 'Christmas is a time when kids tell Santa 